<paragraph id="8BA9B501FFC4FF04FF1A8A17E695FA6E" blockId="21.[151,1437,1317,1992]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
The material used for the re-description of 
<taxonomicName id="4C16CE82FFC4FF04FD198A17E4B5FAE1" authority="(Reid, 1951)" authorityName="Just" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Reid" baseAuthorityYear="1951" box="[660,1023,1317,1344]" class="Malacostraca" family="Synopiidae" genus="Tironella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="altifrons">
<emphasis id="B9626913FFC4FF04FD198A17E429FA9E" box="[660,867,1317,1343]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Tironella altifrons</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF87C8F0FFC4FF04FCFB8A17E4BDFAE1" author="Reid, D. M." box="[886,1015,1317,1344]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="189 - 291" refId="ref50178" refString="Reid, D. M. (1951) Report on the Amphipoda (Gammaridea and Caprellidea) of the Coast of Tropical West Africa. Atlantide Report, 2, 189 - 291." type="journal article" year="1951">Reid, 1951</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
consists of a microvial with a few crushed mouthparts, a dissected torso with a few limbs, a permanent slide with pereopods 5 and 7 (illustrated by Reid, pereopod 5 labeled as 6 by Reid), his published sketches of the head with antennae and the urosome with uropods (both reproduced in 
<figureCitation id="132DA984FFC4FF04FE538AA3E57AFA0A" box="[478,560,1425,1451]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="22.[151,250,1857,1881]" captionTargetBox="[168,1427,197,1826]" captionTargetId="figure-23@22.[151,1436,181,1833]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 10. Tironella altifrons (Reid, 1951) comb. nov. Holotype, ♂. clv, head and antennae; p3, pereopod 3; p.5–7, pereopods 5 to 7; us, urosome. (clv and us from Reid 1951, fig.31)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6572043" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6572043/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
), together with his rather lengthy description. Direct quotes from 
<bibRefCitation id="EF87C8F0FFC4FF04FA988AA3E2D6FA0D" author="Reid, D. M." box="[1301,1436,1425,1452]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="189 - 291" refId="ref50178" refString="Reid, D. M. (1951) Report on the Amphipoda (Gammaridea and Caprellidea) of the Coast of Tropical West Africa. Atlantide Report, 2, 189 - 291." type="journal article" year="1951">Reid (1951)</bibRefCitation>
are given in quotation marks.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
