<subSubSection id="C30CE68AFFC4FF06FF4A895BE558F86B" lastPageId="23" lastPageNumber="24" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BA9B501FFC4FF04FF4A895BE5EBF906" blockId="21.[151,1437,1317,1992]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis id="B9626913FFC4FF04FF4A895BE61BF922" bold="true" box="[199,337,1641,1667]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Description</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B9626913FFC4FF04FEED8958E51AF922" box="[352,592,1641,1668]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Accessory ommatidia</emphasis>
assumed to be present (
<figureCitation id="132DA984FFC4FF04FCD0895BE4E7F922" box="[861,941,1641,1667]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="22.[151,250,1857,1881]" captionTargetBox="[168,1427,197,1826]" captionTargetId="figure-23@22.[151,1436,181,1833]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 10. Tironella altifrons (Reid, 1951) comb. nov. Holotype, ♂. clv, head and antennae; p3, pereopod 3; p.5–7, pereopods 5 to 7; us, urosome. (clv and us from Reid 1951, fig.31)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6572043" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6572043/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
clv): “One pair of eyes is clearly visible but I cannot be sure that I have seen another pair”.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA9B501FFC4FF04FF4A8983E4E3F94E" blockId="21.[151,1437,1317,1992]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis id="B9626913FFC4FF04FF4A8983E600F96A" box="[199,330,1713,1739]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Mouthparts</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B9626913FFC4FF04FEDA8983E688F96A" box="[343,450,1713,1739]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Maxilla 1</emphasis>
palp with 2 short simple, 3 tri-cusped, and a single longer serrate robust setae; outer plate with row of 9 finely serrate pointed robust setae; inner plate damaged.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA9B501FFC4FF04FF4A89C8E7A9F821" blockId="21.[151,1437,1317,1992]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis id="B9626913FFC4FF04FF4A89C8E676F8B2" box="[199,316,1785,1812]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Antenna 1</emphasis>
reaching to middle of article 5 of antenna 2, peduncle second article 0.4 length of article 1, third article 2/3 length of article 2; flagellum subequal in length to peduncle, with 6+ articles; accessory flagellum of 3 articles. 
<emphasis id="B9626913FFC4FF04FF7B8870E622F8FA" box="[246,360,1857,1884]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Antenna 2</emphasis>
peduncular article 5 about 2/3 length of article 4; flagellum of 5 articles. Both antennae sparsely setose.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA9B501FFC4FF04FF4A88BBE4D1F866" blockId="21.[151,1437,1317,1992]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis id="B9626913FFC4FF04FF4A88BBE6E4F802" box="[199,430,1929,1955]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Gnathopods 1 and 2</emphasis>
carpus posterior margin with a few groups of long and short setae; propodus with single stout, pectinate seta and a few long simple setae on posterior margin.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF69E589FFC7FF07FF1A8873E45DF8DC" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6572043" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6572043" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6572043/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" startId="22.[151,250,1857,1881]" targetBox="[168,1427,197,1826]" targetPageId="22">
